modules.description: Provides network protocol parsing and serialization for TCP, UDP, and IP layers, along with packet inspection and modification capabilities. Operates on byte sequences and structured data representations of network headers. Used to implement custom network stacks and packet filtering in unikernel-based cloud services.

Provides type definitions and function signatures for network, block, and time operations, including `connect`, `read`, `write`, and `time` functions. Works with data structures such as buffers, sockets, and time sources to enable low-level system interactions. Used to standardize interface implementations across different backends like TCP, UDP, and disk drivers.
